description:
Datashift is a fast\-growing consultancy team with a focus on delivering solutions that answer business questions with data and facts. For one of our fastest growing practices, we are looking for a skilled
 **Data Engineer** 
 .




 Do you have at least
 **3 to 6 years of experience?** 
 Do you love to work on projects and look at them from an end\-to\-end data perspective. Then we are delighted to receive your personal application and we’ll contact you for an interview and a (virtual) cup of coffee.




**Your Responsibilities**
* Translate client needs into maintainable data solution (ETL/Infrastructure as a code/Interfaces/pipelines, ...);
* Design data solutions, making the trade\-off between cost and maintainability;
* Work together with Data Scientists, BI specialists and Business Consultants to deliver value to our customers;
* Stay up to date with the latest developments in data technology and actively participate in sharing your knowledge with your colleagues;
* Monitor the quality and stability of data solutions;
* Coach other Data Engineers.


**Your Qualifications**
* Programming expertise with Python;
* You feel energized when writing and observing well\-structured code;
* Strong background in development, with knowledge in languages such as Java and/or PHP;
* API Integration skills;
* Experience with pipeline automation (i.e. Airflow)
* Deep knowledge of SQL;
* Experience with AWS/GCP/Azure/Ansible/Terrafom
* Experience with Linux is a plus;
* Fluent in Dutch and/or French and English.


**Your growth path**
* Datashift is a firm believer in growing through its people. We will guide and support you providing many opportunities to develop and grow in the direction you want. However, we equally believe that it is you who takes ownership of your growth. That is why we give you the tools and the driving seat, it's up to you to do seize the opportunity.
* One thing is for sure, surrounded by an entrepreneurial team, many opportunities will present themselves to deepen your expertise knowledge or broaden your Horizon in Data.
* In this role, you are on the track to become a master in leading Data Engineering solutions for our clients. Whilst collaborating within Datashift on existing competence centers or helping to establish new practices. Making sure you and we keep up with the advancements in Data Engineering.


**Our offer**
* A highly entrepreneurial team;
* A no\-nonsense working environment with a focus on high quality;
* Excellent terms of employment (including company car, fuel card, meal vouchers \& bonus);
* Fringe benefits including continuous training that builds and extends professional, technical and management skills in all areas;
* The opportunity to grow together with Datashift in terms of capabilities as well as financial benefits.


**Interested?**
 Don't hesitate to apply via the link below!

We are looking for AI/ML Consultants, who wants to work for the European Institutions in Brussels.




 We are looking for a senior IT consultant with at least 1 year of ML, NLP, AI experience with Python or Java in a cloud environment










 Candidates need to be based in the proximity of 2 hours of Brussels by car. Consultants need to be aware that they need to work 1 to 2 days in the Brussels office.










 EU candidates are welcome to apply. Work permit is not provided.










 This position is also open for employees and freelancers. Candidates need to be fluent in English.










**Tasks and responsibilities** 



* Develop and maintain software applications in Natural Language Processing (NLP), Machine Learning (ML), and Artificial Intelligence (AI);
* Design and optimize machine learning systems and deep learning architectures;
* Collaborate with cross\-functional teams to integrate AI/ML solutions into existing products and processes;
* Define and implement IT architectures for NLP, ML, and AI solutions, ensuring alignment with master and meta\-data management concepts;
* Perform data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model evaluation to enhance performance;
* Stay updated with the latest advancements in AI/ML technologies and algorithms;
* Maintain and support AI\-deployed solutions on SaaS platforms such as AWS and Azure;
* Document architecture blueprints and align them with business requirements;









**Profile:** 



* Master or Bachelor degree;
* \+14 years of general IT experience.
* \+1 year of experience with Large Language Models (LLMs), text embeddings, tokenization, vectorization, machine learning, and deep learning;
* \+1 year of experience with of Python/Java/Containers (Docker/Kubernetes)/Cloud AI services (AWS, Azure);
* \+1 year of experience in the full lifecycle of natural language processing (NLP) systems and agile software development methodologies;
* \+1 year of experience in quality assurance and quality control for machine translation (MT), and experience with MT quality procedures, testing methodologies and tools, such as automatic quality metrics (BLEU scores and similar) and human evaluation of MT quality;
* Proven ability to conduct proof of concepts (PoCs) efficiently and effectively;
* Strong presentation skills for both technical and business audiences;
* High attention to quality standards and the ability to work in fast\-evolving cloud\-based environments;
* Strong written communication skills for technical documentation;
* Ability to actively participate in technical discussions and collaborate with diverse stakeholders;
* Fluent in English;



 Desirable Certifications (one or more of the following certifications are preferred):



* AWS Certifications: AWS Certified Machine Learning, AWS Certified Data Analytics, AWS Certified Solutions Architect;
* Microsoft Certifications: Azure AI Engineer Associate, Azure Data Scientist Associate, Azure Solutions Architect Expert;

A large, socially engaged organization with a robust IT landscape is looking for an experienced Data Engineer to help design, improve, and maintain its central data platform. Your work will directly contribute to smarter decision\-making, better services, and the development of innovative data products.








 Your Role: Bridging Data and Business




 As a Data Engineer, you'll be responsible for setting up, managing, and continuously improving the data platform. Your goal is to ensure data is accurate, accessible, and secure, empowering the business to make informed decisions and enhance overall performance.




 Key responsibilities include:



* Translating data requests into efficient, scalable solutions;
* Designing and maintaining an Enterprise Data Model (EDM) as a semantic layer across all organizational data;
* Modeling data at both logical and physical levels based on conceptual business needs;
* Building data pipelines and lakehouses on modern platforms (e.g. Azure, Databricks, Snowflake);
* Ensuring data quality, clear documentation, and strong governance practices;
* Managing access to data environments in line with internal data policies;
* Collaborating closely with business and IT stakeholders;
* Reporting to the Lead Data Engineer.







 Your Profile: Analytical, Solution\-Oriented \& Communicative



* Master's degree with at least 5 years of experience in data modeling (including Kimball methodology);
* Strong knowledge of SQL, Python, and Pyspark;
* Experience with modern data platforms and BI tools (Cognos, Power BI, Tableau);
* Ability to think abstractly and translate concepts into models and code;
* A proactive team player who gives and receives feedback constructively;
* Familiar with GDPR and agile methodologies;
* Focused on delivering value quickly, while building the EDM iteratively;
* Fluent in Dutch and French.







 About the Organization




 You'll be joining an organization where data and technology are at the core of operations. The internal IT department consists of over 200 professionals who develop tools and applications used daily by thousands of users. With millions of transactions processed each day, your impact will be felt across the country.
